</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9858407FDE0E5A4F1F4DDDBCB4B01C57" pageId="122" pageNumber="123" type="type">
<paragraph id="BCEFCC99C86C575B068EF8EC54BE4759" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="552778FBCD1CEFB462B6324858793B8E" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">
SOMALIA, 
<emphasis id="105F08D089A619774A0CE7FDF1BB2FA0" italics="true" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Recoil</emphasis>
73 (holotype P).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2B7D99938A5C1814FA8A13E1F4BA1358" pageId="122" pageNumber="123" type="description">
<paragraph id="3F0CFD566560CDDE42469AC5AEE00659" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DAB62EF2FC4F818D6D7828955A5E0182" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">
Annual or briefly perennial herb with a small tap root, similar to 
<taxonomicName id="2EFB5DBFB2EACEDEADBE539F3E5D6BB1" authorityName="Hochst. ex Choisy, Prodr. [A. P. de Candolle] 9: 405. (Choisy" authorityYear="1845" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus rhyniospermus" order="Solanales" pageId="122" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhyniospermus">
<emphasis id="1091F6C57960BA6951A44E860D70A529" italics="true" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Convolvulus rhyniospermus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; stems usually numerous, decumbent or ascending from the base to 40 cm, but usually much less; vegetative parts pubescent. Leaves subsessile, 0.5-6 
<normalizedToken id="67752936DA69248E48C26EDC3E7B1F25" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.2-1.8 cm, oblong or, less commonly, oblanceolate or elliptic, obtuse and sometimes mucronulate, entire, cuneate at the base into an indistinct petiole. Flowers many, in subsessile, bracteate heads forming an elongate leafy inflorescence; peduncles 0-0.4 mm; bracteoles 4-9 
<normalizedToken id="59681DAA272C81FBD84E7386A9D70FBA" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-3 mm, linear, oblong-elliptic or lanceolate, acute, ciliate especially in the lower half; sepals 5-7 
<normalizedToken id="AAA2043A6FDDE9C4CA0B8A230B190CDF" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5-2.5 mm, ovate, acute, pilose and strongly ciliate, the outer sepals c. 1 mm wider than the inner ones; corolla blue, 7-12 mm long, shallowly lobed, midpetaline bands with a few inconspicuous hairs; ovary glabrous, style glabrous, divided 2.5 mm above base, stigmas linear, 2-3 mm, slightly widened towards apex and sometimes unequal. Capsule glabrous, seeds papillate. [
<bibRefCitation id="2B657EA1CB977F02DFAFFCBC9C2C18C1" author="Verdcourt, B" editor="Hubbard, CE" journalOrPublisher="HMSO, London" pageId="213" pageNumber="214" pagination="1 - 161" refId="B373" refString="Verdcourt, B, 1963. Convolvulaceae. In: Hubbard, CE, Milne-Redhead, E, Eds., Flora of Tropical East Africa. HMSO, London: 1 - 161" title="Convolvulaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of Tropical East Africa." year="1963">Verdcourt 1963</bibRefCitation>
: 40 (as 
<taxonomicName id="C76A938D8F3CEA3BDF8EA533683993B1" authorityName="Hochst. ex Choisy, Prodr. [A. P. de Candolle] 9: 405. (Choisy" authorityYear="1845" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus rhyniospermus" order="Solanales" pageId="122" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhyniospermus">
<emphasis id="802116EFFF9D9A3DE01175F131E92BC2" italics="true" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Convolvulus rhyniospermus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); 
<bibRefCitation id="44D3CE92470E60C7DCF036DE1C2C6988" author="Verdcourt, B" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="213" pageNumber="214" pagination="459 - 464" publicationUrl="10.2307/4110047" refId="B375" refString="Verdcourt, B, 1982. Corrections and additions to the &quot;Flora of Tropical East Africa: Convolvulaceae &quot; V. Kew Bulletin 37: 459 - 464, DOI: 10.2307/4110047" title="Corrections and additions to the &quot; Flora of Tropical East Africa: Convolvulaceae &quot; V." url="10.2307/4110047" volume="37" year="1982">Verdcourt 1982</bibRefCitation>
: 461; 
<bibRefCitation id="B81B3C65A6F4B22230DC8040E3259D54" author="Sebsebe, D" editor="Hedberg, I" journalOrPublisher="National Herbarium Addis Ababa University &amp; Department of Systematic Botany, Uppsala University" pageId="211" pageNumber="212" pagination="161 - 231" refId="B330" refString="Sebsebe, D, 2006. Convolvulaceae. In: Hedberg, I, Ensermu, K, Edwards, S, Sebsebe, Demissew, Persson, E, Eds., Flora of Ethiopia &amp; Eritrea 5: Gentianaceae to Cyclocheilaceae. National Herbarium Addis Ababa University &amp; Department of Systematic Botany, Uppsala University: 161 - 231" title="Convolvulaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of Ethiopia &amp; Eritrea 5: Gentianaceae to Cyclocheilaceae." year="2006">Sebsebe 2006</bibRefCitation>
181]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DEAF4979957D08D29727903F48B78525" pageId="122" pageNumber="123" type="notes">
<paragraph id="4CB0B07752E73AB2E0EEEE7FF6C0C12D" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FC7FB09FF5CA172D8224BF244FD0655A" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">
This species is quite variable, approaching 
<taxonomicName id="7F7E206AA2834337C2B59718F79BB5E5" authorityName="Verdc., Kew Bull. 12: 344. 1957. (Verdcourt" authorityYear="1957" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus jefferyi" order="Solanales" pageId="122" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jefferyi">
<emphasis id="C485D45837B1CCF0CBC4C751D8298185" italics="true" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Convolvulus jefferyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="47956C212ED95FF13408603990F34A25" authorityName="Chiov., Fl. Somala 1: 229. 1929. (Chiovenda" authorityYear="1929" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus stenocladus" order="Solanales" pageId="122" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stenocladus">
<emphasis id="314A070C8C0ED3C6029CC9BBE0BEA070" italics="true" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Convolvulus stenocladus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see discussion under both species) at one extreme and 
<taxonomicName id="3FEC888833C34D5C50E8E3BBE036EEDD" authorityName="Hochst. ex Choisy, Prodr. [A. P. de Candolle] 9: 405. (Choisy" authorityYear="1845" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus rhyniospermus" order="Solanales" pageId="122" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhyniospermus">
<emphasis id="E061A21326D7DCA3A1E64A4CD5C50D06" italics="true" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Convolvulus rhyniospermus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at the other. Specimens without corollas cannot be safely separated from 
<taxonomicName id="6A34F51960BD902E1494B4A0346F6C4A" authorityName="Hochst. ex Choisy, Prodr. [A. P. de Candolle] 9: 405. (Choisy" authorityYear="1845" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus rhyniospermus" order="Solanales" pageId="122" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhyniospermus">
<emphasis id="D14416304B8B65C4019F8B3B1E2193F7" italics="true" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Convolvulus rhyniospermus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Following 
<bibRefCitation id="A22165A3EFDDF5F42793970CF65FC7AE" author="Verdcourt, B" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="213" pageNumber="214" pagination="459 - 464" publicationUrl="10.2307/4110047" refId="B375" refString="Verdcourt, B, 1982. Corrections and additions to the &quot;Flora of Tropical East Africa: Convolvulaceae &quot; V. Kew Bulletin 37: 459 - 464, DOI: 10.2307/4110047" title="Corrections and additions to the &quot; Flora of Tropical East Africa: Convolvulaceae &quot; V." url="10.2307/4110047" volume="37" year="1982">Verdcourt (1982)</bibRefCitation>
, we recognise two infraspecific taxa, their extremes being very different in appearance:
</paragraph>
